.\" termin.al-name: about
.\" termin.al-usage: about
.\" termin.al-summary: Open about content.
.TH ABOUT 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
about \- Open about content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
about
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the fixed virtual document
.B ~/about.md
as rendered Markdown in the inline viewer owned by the current shell pane.
.SH VIEWER
The viewer supports j/k or arrow-key movement, PageUp/b and PageDown/Space paging, g/G jumps, / search, n/N match navigation, and q or Escape to return. Returning restores the same shell transcript, history and working directory.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. A missing document produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic; cancellation returns no viewer.
.SH NOTES
The published document and virtual filesystem are read-only. Mobile controls provide Escape, movement and the pane Prefix action.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ about
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
open(1), help(1), man(1)
